trans-unit.source: Public instance fields exist on every created instance of a class. By declaring a public field, you can ensure the field is always present, and the class definition is more self-documenting.
trans-unit.target: 公共实例字段存在于类的每个创建实例上。通过声明一个公共字段,可以确保该字段始终存在,而且类的定义更加自洽。

trans-unit.source: Public static fields are declared using the static keyword. They are added to the class constructor at the time of class evaluation using Object.defineProperty(). They are accessed again from the class constructor.
trans-unit.target: 公共静态字段使用 static 关键字声明。使用 Object.defineProperty() 在类评估时将它们添加到类构造函数中。从类构造函数可以再次访问它们。

trans-unit.source: Public static fields are not reinitialized on subclasses, but can be accessed via the prototype chain.
trans-unit.target: 公共静态字段不会在子类上重新初始化,但可以通过原型链访问。

trans-unit.source: Public static fields are useful when you want a field to exist only once per class, not on every class instance you create. This is useful for caches, fixed-configuration, or any other data you don't need to be replicated across instances.
trans-unit.target: 当你希望一个字段在每个类中只存在一次,而不是在你创建的每个类实例上存在时,公共静态字段就很有用。这对于缓存、固定配置或任何其他不需要跨实例复制的数据都很有用。
